Nigeria is in dire need of N5bn to procure 229,636 cartons of Ready to Use Therapeutic Food (RUTF) needed to address severe acute malnutrition cases in Borno, Adamawa and Yobe States in the coming year, the United Nations Children FundsÂ  has said. UNICEF Nutrition Specialists Aminu Usman at a media dialogue yesterday on Child Malnutrition, #StopChildMalnutritionNigeria revealed that UNICEF has been able to secure procurement for 29,314 cartons leaving the funding gap at N4.4bn for the procurement of 229,636 cartons of RUTF. He noted the likelihood of fresh influx that might aggravate the already poor nutrition situation in the states. FG spends N1.8bn on prevention, treatment of malnutrition in 18 states UNICEF treats 1m children suffering from malnutrition in Nigeria Malnutrition: NGO advocates for establishment of more CMAM centres in Bauchi OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY